(792, 'Chiesa di Santa Scolastica a Rieti', 'The church of Santa Scolastica is one of the deconsecrated religious buildings of Rieti, now housing the Varrone Auditorium between its walls. It was built by order of nuns to replace the old church of Saint Andrew, designed by architect Francesco Fontana and was constructed between 1696 and 1717. A travertine arcade, leads the way into the Greek cross interior with two side chapels and a high dome illuminated by eight clerestory windows. The apse, decorated by Philip Brioni in 1745, was later enriched with polychrome marbles and gilded stuccoes. In the Napoleonic era, the church of Santa Scolastica was deconsecrated and thus housed the offices of the court and later a prison, before becoming a chapel for students of the nearby ecclesiastic college.', 42.4041, 12.859, ''),
