(2288, 'Mura e Porte - Ferentino', 'The walls of Ferentino, surrounding most of the built-up area for a length of about 2.5 km, are the result and the testimony of the origin of the town, which holds valuable Roman and medieval monuments.Not all historians agree in dating the first construction of the walls, and some of them believe that the Pelasgians, ancient people of Mediterranean sailors, were the first builders. More likely, the present appearance is due to the changes made at the time of the Roman conquest, around 400 BC, while towers and gates were added or modified during the Middle Ages.The walls are made of huge megalithic blocks one after the other so as to fit perfectly and give strength to the structure without the use of lime or any other binder. The first layer is made with regular blocks arranged in horizontal rows, and above it, another layer of medieval age built by alternating regular and irregular blocks.Inside, there are the walls of the Acropolis, which extend for 550 meters.Between the two walls, it''s possible to admire the polygonal terraces, called Ieroni, made to defend the three most important gates of the town: Porta Sant''Agata, Porta Maggiore or Santa Maria and Porta Montana. In addition to these three gates, along the perimeter of the walls, there are also Porta Montana, Porta San Francesco and la Sangunaria (the bloody gate). The latter, located south of the town, is the best preserved and its name recalls the bloody battles that took place near it or the passage of those sentenced to death, escorted to the Aia del Monticchio below to be executed. In the walls beside the door there are traces of three different eras: the base dates back to pre-Roman age (fourth century BC); over the arch, the travertine work with two empty square, perhaps created to lighten the weight of the arch itself, is of Roman origin (second century BC). Over the travertine, it''s still visible the medieval wall with rectangular holes arranged at regular intervals, which could be used as supports for the wooden scaffoldings.', 41.6927, 13.2534, ''),
